<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=203307">Craegor Icewulf 47 Warrior</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bellia>Bellia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#333333>(12/16/02 6:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1712.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.belliapics.homestead.com/files/bellia.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Call of Arch Mage Questions</span><hr size=1> Magic resists also effect charm (61 levels of charm kiting experience talking here) so get your best malo on the mob before charming.  I usually put tash, tinku malo's then I charm.  Either my pets last under a minute (quick break) or they last nearly full duration with my 260 cha. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Mistress Bellia Divinewind</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Tinku's lvl 61 Phantasmist Pet<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231078">I am ghetto</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kelebekchannelar>KelebekChannelar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 264<br> <font col