A 30ft Earth Elemental that quads for 471 with BO5 is a scary scary thing. LOL. <br>
<br>
I would be careful buffing these guys though really. Not only are they mean as hell when charm breaks, but once I had to zone and charmed a different MOB once I got back in. A 2 group miniraid unsuspectingly pulled my ex-pet which still had BO5, and it owned them in about 30 seconds. I think they thought the cool looking sword it was wielding was something other than a Blade of Walnan bahahaha. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=perplexbamboozeler>Perplex Bamboozeler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#333333>(12/17/02 6:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1712.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Call of Arch Mage Questions</span><hr size=1> &quot;I would be careful buffing these guys though really. Not only are they mean as hell when charm breaks,&quot;<br>
