<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ringofvalor.com">Ring of Valor</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kalahadbb>KalahadBB</A> at: 12/17/02 12:15:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iwanthewicca>IwanTheWicca</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#333333>(12/21/02 4:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1712.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Call of the Arch Magi = Tunare's Request?</span><hr size=1> Since Magicians, like Druids and Necros, can only charm one type of NPC, should this spell be modified to be a non-aggro spell?<br>
<br>
For example, Tunare's Request is a lvl 50+ Druid charm which causes no aggro to the charmed animal when charm breaks. Would it not be wise to make Call of the Arch Magi on the same principal? That way a quick taunt by the warrior of the group and a recasted Charm by the Mage = a now safe pet. Since we lack Root/Snare/Mez unlike the other 3 charming classes, I can only see this as more of an excuse for us to have Call of the Arch Magi as a no-aggro spell. let's not forget that Glamour of Tunare is a no-aggro -20 MR debuff too.<br>
<br>
Of course, when played correctly, the aggro caused by Charm is of little consequence to Magicians in an experienced group of players. Another Enchanter/Magician could quickly Mez the offending elemental while the Cleric heals the bruised Mage as he/she re-casts Call of the Arch Magi.<br>
<br>
I would not be surprised of later expansions give Mages an extended Charm/Mez line of spells even if it is only from Level 51-65. Before you know it we may be getting elemental only roots and slows <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I can see these new spells having a profound affect on the Mage class on the expansions to come.<br>
<br>
But can Call of the Arch Magi become 0 aggro? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
